text: Jasper County is a county in the U.S. state of Indiana. As of 2020, 32,918 people lived there. The county seat is Rensselaer. == History == Jasper County was created in 1838. It was named after Sgt. William Jasper, a famous scout for the Continental Army during the American Revolutionary War. == Geography == According to the 2010 census, the county has a total area of , of which (or 99.68%) is land and (or 0.31%) is water. === Bordering counties === == Municipalities == The municipalities in Jasper County, and their populations as of the 2020 census, are: === Cities === * Rensselaer â€“ 5,733 === Towns === === Census-designated places === == Townships == The 13 townships of Jasper County, with their populations as of the 2020 census, are: == References == == Other websites == * Category:1838 establishments in Indiana Category:Indiana counties
